    <text>
        <body>
        	<div1 type="letter">
        		<pb entity="DSSR_000001108_0157"/>
        		<head>Jim to Monsieur Paul Rockwell, Sat.  <date value="1916-05-20">May 20th [1916]</date></head>
        		
        		<opener>
            <dateline>Sat. <date value="1916-05-20">May 20th [1916]</date></dateline>
            
            <salute>Dear Paul:</salute>
        		</opener>
        		
            <p>
            I wonder if you
            received my wire re Kiffin’s
            Boche?  I beat Noel to
            it but am afraid wire
            was hung up.  Anyway
            Kiffin wrote you.  Its
            great to have had
            Kiffin bring one down.  The
            Boches got peeved and
            dropped bombs on us
            yesterday and to day.  This
            morning they killed five,
            wounded others and burnt
            up three of our tractors.
            They came in the dark
            
            <pb entity="DSSR_000001108_0159" n="[p.2]"/>
            
            and we couldn’t do
            anything about it.  We
            received orders to go to
            Bar le duc and the escadrille
            flew off and moved off
            this A. M. leaving me to
            hold down Luxeuil.  A
            damn little thing for the 
            tail that is coming from
            Paris is holding me up.
            I’ll go via Toul and
            look up my old friend
            Capt. Wall.
            </p><p>
            Norman Prince
            ran out of snow and
            busted up on way
            
            <pb entity="DSSR_000001108_0158" n="[p.3]"/>
            
            out.  Cowden when he
            gets thru [sic] with Paris
            will come here to get 
            his machine.
            </p><p>
            Yes, the Committee
            kicked thru [sic].  It seems
            gros [sic]: got most of the
            money to use for whatever
            purpose he deemed best 
            and so we haven’t much
            of a hold on him.
            </p><p>
            Kiffin may get a thousand
            frcs [francs ?] from the Committee
            for reward with Nudaille.
            Won’t he be some
            swank tho [sic] with medals
            
            <pb entity="DSSR_000001108_0160" n="[p.4]"/>
            
            all over him!  He could
            have had anything in this
            town.
            </p><p>
            God knows when I’m 
            going to get away from 
            here but I hope soon.
            I’m alone and it seems
            queer.  Please thank Mrs.
            Weeks for her letter and
            say I’ll write soon.  Glad
            you thought to give her
            the candy.
            </p>
        		
        		<closer>
            <salute>My best</salute>   
            
            <signed>Jim</signed>
            
            <seg type="postscript">
            New secteur is No. 8<lb/>
            <lb/>
            Escadrille N. 124<lb/>
            S.P. No. 8.
            </seg>
        		</closer>
        		
            
